g.text: 1.Pod sends DNS Request to CoreDNS2.CoreDNS realizes that the request is for an external domain, and sends it to Upstream DNS Server.Upstream DNS Server responds back, and the Pod received the IP address.3.Pod sends traffic to the endpoint, through the Nodes Interface4.The Node sends traffic to the Load Balancer5.Load Balancer NATs the traffic and sends the packet to the destination using its own Public IP address.
